_source.text: 403 Some of the limitations of traditional beta-blockers do not appear to be shared by some of the vasodilating beta-blockers, such as celiprolol, carvedilol and nebivolol-more widely used today-which reduce central pulse pressure and aortic stiffness better than atenolol or metoprolol 404 - 406 and affect insulin sensitivity less than metoprolol.
